description.narrative: (Jordan): .The Jordan Competitiveness Program (JCP) fosters sustainable economic growth by enhancing Jordan's competitiveness, improving the business enabling environment and increasing employment, investment and exports within targeted sectors. JCP focuses on developing key drivers of competitiveness for targeted clusters with high growth potential through improving the business enabling environment, business development at the firm level and supporting sector associations to attract investment. Target sectors include information and communication technology (ICT), clean technologies and health sciences/medical services. JCP supports economic reforms in accordance with the Jordan Compact by providing policy, legal and regulatory assistance to the Government of Jordan. A key element of JCP's approach is strengthening Jordan's innovation network - connecting public, private, and academic organizations and individuals, both domestically and internationally. .
